Good morning,

The Stratechery Plus bundle is expanding in a fun new direction with the ad=
dition of Greatest of All Talk ( https://goat.passport.online/member ) , a =
podcast about basketball, life, and national parks:

My initial relationship with my Sharp Tech ( https://sharptech.fm/ ) co-hos=
t Andrew Sharp was a one-way one: I was an ardent listener of the Sports Il=
lustrated Open Floor podcast he hosted with fellow writer Ben Golliver ( ht=
tps://twitter.com/BenGolliver ). Open Floor was both quirky and knowledgabl=
e, with the sort of conversational tone I like in podcasts, and it rewarded=
 loyal listeners with ongoing gags and inside jokes.

Fast forward a couple of years =E2=80=94 at which point I had had the chanc=
e to become real-life friends with Sharp =E2=80=94 and new Sports Illustrat=
ed owner Maven laid off half of the staff ( https://www.npr.org/2019/10/03/=
766929743/new-owners-of-sports-illustrated-set-massive-layoffs-journalists-=
rebel ) , including Sharp, which meant the end of my favorite podcast. That=
=E2=80=99s when I had the chance to meet Golliver, and pushed the two of th=
em to launch an independent for-pay podcast called The Greatest Of All Talk=
 ( https://greatestofalltalk.com/ ) , or GOAT for short. That was four year=
s ago, and the GOAT became my new favorite podcast, for all of the same rea=
sons =E2=80=94 but now with no ads, and a thriving community to boot.

Over that period Sharp left journalism for the law, but when he decided he =
wanted to come back to media, I jumped at the opportunity to work with him =
here at Stratechery, first on Sharp Tech, and then Sharp China with Bill Bi=
shop ( https://sharpchina.fm/ ). And now, to bring things full circle, I=E2=
=80=99m thrilled to add GOAT to the Stratechery Plus bundle. If you like ba=
sketball, acerbic humor, great chemistry, and the reward of being a loyal l=
istener, GOAT is, well, a GOAT-level ( https://www.urbandictionary.com/defi=
ne.php?term=3Dgoat ) podcast.

A quick note for anyone who is already a GOAT-listener: GOAT will remain an=
 independent entity that listeners can subscribe to directly; however, it i=
s now available to all Stratechery Plus subscribers as well. If you are a s=
ubscriber to both and don=E2=80=99t want to double-pay, you can cancel your=
 subscription on GOAT=E2=80=99s hosting service ( https://goat.supportingca=
st.fm/request_access ) and add a new feed on Passport ( https://goat.passpo=
rt.online/ ) (or using the links in this email).

I hope you enjoy the show as much as I do.

On to the update, where I want to follow-up on a few stories I=E2=80=99ve c=
overed in these first few weeks.

Twitter Timelines
-----------------

Twitter is finally out with an explanation as to why it killed off third-pa=
rty developers:

( https://twitter.com/TwitterDev/status/1615405842735714304?ref_src=3Dtwsrc=
